  (74201505, 43018759, '(untitled)', NULL, '[Daily Log Notes] 
Wants over-communication regarding Schedule and Deliverables. Paul, check in daily.

Wants confirmation about plaster schedule with impending rain.

Will be away Thursday and Friday - WORK CANNOT BE DONE ON THESE DAYS

Wants a written schedule for the next deliverables - Carter

Hook up the lights again. Will need wire.

Adding 4 more ficus hedge plants and 1 more creeping ficus.

Hook up irrigation to pots through the ground. Make sure the irrigated pots are using the same irrigation lines for succulents. We may need extra rock for mulch in the Pool Enclosure area.

Make sure everything is cleaned up! Pick up screws and leftover wires, tubes, etc.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '(.PM) Carter Godley'),
  (74202224, 42580132, '(untitled)', NULL, '[Daily Log Notes] 
- Uncover & move soil off the boulders and plants on slope. they are buried.

- Change Order for additional plantings pending

Irrigation Heads
- Can we change to pop up heads? Why are they so tall

Lights:
- New lights are too dim
- Move some lights closer to fence? Do a night-time visit for lighting assessment
- Existing uplight on Chinese Elm no longer working; re-wire
- Once we get confirmation about the lighting strength, homeowner will decide on rear lighting

- Mex. beach pebble around pool enclosure: were they moved? where did existing beach pebble go?

- Do a more thorough weeding (see photos)

- Once planting in rear hedge is complete, bury the irrigation lines!

- Clean-up gravel from street and artificial turf areas

- Do thorough clean-up once job completes', NULL, NULL, NULL, '(.PM) Jorge Flores'),
